"text":"follower, of a right way; one directed aright"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) And one says, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaA ri$odiynu","text_ar":"يَا رِشْدِينُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", as meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaA raA$idu","text_ar":"يَا رَاشِدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O thou who takest,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"followest, a right way"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (L)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlxulafaA='u Alr~aA$iduwna","text_ar":"الخُلَفَا=ءُ الرَّاشِدُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The Khaleefehs who took,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"followed, a right course,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the orthodox Khaleefehs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is an appellation specially applied to Aboo-Bekr, 'Omar, 'Othmán, and 'Alee; but applicable also to any others of the Imáms who pursued the same course as those four. (L.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~u raA$idK","text_ar":"اُمُّ رَاشِدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"a surname (S) applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The female rat"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mouse"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfaA^urapu","text_ar":"الفَاُرَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"). (S, K.)"}],"source_refs":["L","S"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}